<div class="container" style="padding-top: var(--space-12); padding-bottom: var(--space-16);">
  <div class="container--prose">

    <header style="margin-bottom: var(--space-10); padding-bottom: var(--space-6); border-bottom: 3px solid var(--color-ink);">
      <h1 style="font-family: var(--font-masthead); font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 5vw, 3.815rem); margin-bottom: var(--space-4);">Submit a Piece</h1>
      <p style="font-size: var(--text-lg); color: var(--color-ink-muted); font-style: italic; max-width: 55ch;">
        Have something to share? We would love to hear from you.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="article-body">

      <h2>Letters to the Editor</h2>

      <p>Have a thought about something you read on The Traveling Times? Want to respond to an article, share your own travel story, or recommend a poem? Send us a letter at <a href="mailto:{{ site.email }}">{{ site.email }}</a>.</p>

      <p>Include your first name and the article you are responding to (if applicable). Letters may be edited for length and clarity. We publish a selection, not all submissions.</p>

      <h2>Submit a Piece</h2>

      <p>If you would like to contribute an original piece to The Traveling Times — a poem, a travel story, a review, artwork, or anything creative — send it to <a href="mailto:{{ site.email }}">{{ site.email }}</a> with "Submission" in the subject line.</p>

      <p>Please include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your name (or pen name)</li>
        <li>What kind of piece it is (poem, essay, review, art, etc.)</li>
        <li>The piece itself, pasted into the email or attached</li>
      </ul>

      <p>We will get back to you if we plan to feature your work. Thank you for sharing your creativity with us!</p>

    </div>
  </div>
</div>
